    <Dinner>True</Dinner>
    <Gameday>False</Gameday>
    <Comfort>False</Comfort>
    <Sweet>False</Sweet>
    <Slowcooker>False</Slowcooker>
    <Paleo>False</Paleo>
    <Vegan>False</Vegan>
    <Vegetarian>False</Vegetarian>
    <Salad>False</Salad>
    <Soup>False</Soup>
    <Whole30>False</Whole30>
    <Appetizer>False</Appetizer>
    <Glutenfree>False</Glutenfree>
    <RecipeID>0</RecipeID>
    <ImagePath>Images/Chicken Fajita Bake.jpg</ImagePath>
    <Instructions>1. preheat the oven to 400 F.
2. grease a 9x13 baking pan, and place chicken breasts in it.
3. evenly coat each side of the chicken breasts with the fajita seasoning.
4. slice the bell peppers into thin strips and spread evenly on top of the chicken breasts.
                    *For info on how to make your own Fajita Seasoning, consult                       
                      the cookbook
5. top the chicken and peppers with cheese and bake, uncovered for 20-30 minutes. exact time will vary based on the thickness of the breasts.
6. serve with salsa and/or sour cream
7. enjoy!</Instructions>
