  <Recipe>
    <Name>Whole30 Gravy</Name>
    <Ingredients>
      <Ingredient>
        <IngredientName>Fat of choice (grease from sausage, Ghee, or olive oil)</IngredientName>
        <IngredientAmount>3</IngredientAmount>
        <IngredientUnit>tbsp</IngredientUnit>
      </Ingredient>
      <Ingredient>
        <IngredientName>Tapioca powder</IngredientName>
        <IngredientAmount>3</IngredientAmount>
        <IngredientUnit>tbsp</IngredientUnit>
      </Ingredient>
      <Ingredient>
        <IngredientName>Almond or cashew milk</IngredientName>
        <IngredientAmount>2</IngredientAmount>
        <IngredientUnit>cups</IngredientUnit>
      </Ingredient>
      <Ingredient>
        <IngredientName>salt &amp; pepper</IngredientName>
        <IngredientAmount>1/2</IngredientAmount>
        <IngredientUnit>tsp</IngredientUnit>
      </Ingredient>
      <Ingredient>
        <IngredientName>Whole30 approved sausage</IngredientName>
        <IngredientAmount>1</IngredientAmount>
        <IngredientUnit>lb</IngredientUnit>
      </Ingredient>
    </Ingredients>
    <Breakfast>True</Breakfast>
    <Lunch>False</Lunch>
    <Dinner>False</Dinner>
    <Gameday>False</Gameday>
    <Comfort>True</Comfort>
    <Sweet>False</Sweet>
    <Slowcooker>False</Slowcooker>
    <Paleo>False</Paleo>
    <Vegan>False</Vegan>
    <Vegetarian>False</Vegetarian>
    <Salad>False</Salad>
    <Soup>False</Soup>
    <Whole30>True</Whole30>
    <Appetizer>False</Appetizer>
    <Glutenfree>False</Glutenfree>
    <RecipeID>0</RecipeID>
    <ImagePath>Images/Whole30 Gravy.jpg</ImagePath>
    <Instructions>1. in a large sauce pan, brown the sausage.
2. add your fat of choice. (if you think there is already around 3 tbsp of fat in the pan, no need to add more)
3. stir in the tapioca flour until it evenly coats all the pieces of sausage in the pan.
4. add the almond milk and bring to a simmer, stirring occasionally. wait until sauce is thick. It is always better to add the milk bit by bit so your gravy is not too runny. 
5. serve over whole30 hashbrowns and enjoy! a healthier alternative to gravy.

NOTE: For this recipe, the fat i use is Ghee (Clarified butter) which can be found at most local grocery stores.</Instructions>
